33:23.501 --> 33:26.129
Looks like somebody had a little talk
with Ray before they shot him.

33:26.204 --> 33:29.537
- Looks like he held out pretty good.
- He didn't have it.

33:31.509 --> 33:34.410
He couldn't tell them where the money
was, because he didn't know.

33:34.479 --> 33:36.037
Helene hid it.

33:36.114 --> 33:37.103
(SCOFFS)

33:37.482 --> 33:40.144
Ray made poor relationship choices.

33:40.618 --> 33:43.553
Guess they didn't believe him.

33:43.621 --> 33:45.054
Poor prick.

33:45.123 --> 33:47.523
HELENE: I'm not waiting
in a fucking car.

33:55.233 --> 33:57.793
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

34:02.907 --> 34:06.604
- Where's the money, Helene?
- I give a fuck about the money.

34:07.378 --> 34:09.972
- Helene...
- I just want my daughter home with me.

34:10.047 --> 34:14.485
I know it. I know, I'm... I'm sorry.
It's very upsetting about Ray. But...

34:15.420 --> 34:17.320
- Where's the money?
- It's right there.

34:17.388 --> 34:20.789
- Where?
- Buried it when Ray was passed out.

34:21.525 --> 34:22.550
NICK: What was that book about,

34:22.627 --> 34:25.687
Everything You Need
Is in Your Own Backyard?

34:25.763 --> 34:29.130
- I think it was a French book.
- Yeah, that wasn't a book.

34:29.199 --> 34:31.327
- That was a book.
- No, it was a cartoon.

34:31.402 --> 34:32.926
- The fuck out of here.
- No, it was a cartoon.

34:33.004 --> 34:35.199
- Right, Helene?
- Fuck youse both.

34:35.273 --> 34:36.433
Should we bring in the FBI
at this point?

34:36.507 --> 34:38.771
- That's the worst thing we could do.
- Why is that?

34:38.842 --> 34:40.674
'Cause I don't wanna see Cheese
kill Amanda

34:40.745 --> 34:42.042
after he opens a bag
full of newspapers.

34:42.112 --> 34:43.545
It's kidnapping.

34:43.614 --> 34:47.277
- I don't see a note. You see a note?
- Nope. No note.

34:47.351 --> 34:49.581
We're investigating
a missing children's case, here.

34:49.654 --> 34:53.054
Kidnapping has nothing to do with it.
Fastest way to get Amanda home

34:53.123 --> 34:56.116
is go to Cheese,
swap the money for her and walk away.

34:56.194 --> 34:59.630
- Plain and simple.
- Do you know Cheese?

34:59.697 --> 35:03.155
Knew his brother better, Jude.
He was a sweet kid.

35:03.234 --> 35:05.202
Cheese went another way.

35:06.237 --> 35:09.638
- He wouldn't hurt her, right?
- NICK: (CHUCKLES) Ask Ray.

35:09.707 --> 35:11.504
All right, listen.
All he cares about is his money.

35:11.576 --> 35:13.976
If he gets it back...
He's not gonna hurt Amanda.

35:14.045 --> 35:17.572
Just keep your mouth shut, okay?
We'll get her back. It'll be fine.

35:17.648 --> 35:19.946
- Oh, you're gonna talk to him?
- Yeah, that's the idea.

35:20.017 --> 35:22.178
Okay. Well, tell him I'm sorry, all right?

35:22.253 --> 35:24.915
I mean, he knows me,
just tell him I apologize.

35:24.989 --> 35:27.822
Yeah, I'm sure that'll fix everything.
Just take her home.

35:27.892 --> 35:31.020
- We'll take care of this, all right?
- We'll meet you over there.

35:31.095 --> 35:32.494
I'm hungry.

35:32.563 --> 35:33.860
All right. I'll get you something, Helene.

35:33.931 --> 35:35.558
No, her.

35:35.633 --> 35:37.601
That's what she said to me
right before I put her to bed.

35:37.668 --> 35:40.193
She said, "I'm hungry."
I mean, they fed her, right?

35:40.271 --> 35:42.330
She's not still hungry?

35:43.741 --> 35:45.003
I don't know.

36:21.212 --> 36:23.680
(MAN CHATTERING ON RADIO)

36:24.248 --> 36:26.409
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

36:32.256 --> 36:34.053
(WAILS) I know I fucked up.

36:35.193 --> 36:36.421
I just want my daughter back.

36:36.494 --> 36:40.294
(CRYING) I swear to God,
I won't use no drugs no more.

36:40.364 --> 36:42.195
I won't even go out,
I'll be fucking straight.

36:42.266 --> 36:43.858
Cross my heart.

36:45.169 --> 36:47.194
It's all right.
We're gonna find her, Helene.

36:47.271 --> 36:49.330
You have to. You promise?

36:51.209 --> 36:54.110
Yeah. I'm gonna try. I will.

36:55.479 --> 36:58.676
Promise. You have to promise me.

37:00.418 --> 37:01.749
I promise.

37:06.724 --> 37:07.816
All right.

37:25.209 --> 37:26.198
REMY: Where do you
think you're going?

37:26.277 --> 37:27.301
PATRICK: Talk to Cheese.

37:27.378 --> 37:29.039
REMY: No, you're not.
No, get back in the car.

37:29.113 --> 37:31.673
PATRICK: No, that's a mistake.
He's never gonna talk to a badge.

37:31.749 --> 37:33.148
REMY: No. No way.
NICK: It's too important.

37:33.217 --> 37:34.741
You wanna get the girl back, or not?

37:35.253 --> 37:36.948
I know him.
If there's a deal to be brokered,

37:37.021 --> 37:39.080
- we're the ones who can do it.
- No, me and Nick are handling this.

37:39.156 --> 37:40.145
Get back in the car.

37:40.224 --> 37:42.988
Guys, you two go in there
and negotiate a ransom for a little girl,

37:43.060 --> 37:46.461
then it is the FBI.
'Cause it's kidnapping.

37:46.530 --> 37:47.690
ANGIE: All you're gonna do
is scare him.

37:47.765 --> 37:50.495
The more you scare him,
the worse it is for her.

37:52.503 --> 37:54.130
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

37:55.239 --> 37:57.002
All right. Go ahead.

37:57.475 --> 38:01.775
Just fucking relax, sit tight. I know him.
I'm gonna take care of it.

38:01.846 --> 38:03.313
Good luck.

38:09.720 --> 38:11.449
It's been a long time.

38:14.525 --> 38:16.720
No. I quit.

38:23.801 --> 38:26.201
I'm gonna talk some private shit.

38:27.772 --> 38:32.334
- Don't wait, but don't get too far.
- You know I'll be right here.

38:34.412 --> 38:36.778
Bitches love the cheddar.

38:42.687 --> 38:45.781
- How you been, Chris?
- Better than you.

38:48.225 --> 38:50.284
Yeah. Good to hear it.

38:50.361 --> 38:53.455
- Fuck you.
- Man, be cool.

38:53.531 --> 38:57.433
It's been too long not to see a fool.

38:57.501 --> 38:59.492
I grant you audience.

39:00.638 --> 39:01.627
Go.

39:03.140 --> 39:06.268
We found what you
were looking for in Chelsea.

39:07.545 --> 39:09.445
What I care about Chelsea?

39:09.513 --> 39:12.710
'Cause one of the idiots
that robbed you lived there.

39:12.783 --> 39:14.717
What idiot?

39:14.785 --> 39:18.846
The one that you and Chris
beat with a pipe and shot in the chest.

39:20.825 --> 39:24.022
I don't know about nobody getting kill.

39:24.995 --> 39:27.759
But if somebody rob me
and end up dead...

39:28.899 --> 39:32.960
Well, you know, life is a motherfucker.

39:35.473 --> 39:39.671
Cheese, we got your money.
It was buried in Ray's backyard.

39:41.112 --> 39:44.604
We wanna give it back to you
in exchange for Amanda McCready.

39:44.782 --> 39:48.047
The two police outside
are the only other people who know.

39:48.119 --> 39:50.553
No one gives a fuck
about what you did.

39:50.621 --> 39:52.782
I mean, I didn't even
like Ray that much.

39:52.857 --> 39:55.621
You're gonna get your money,
the mother gets her daughter back,

39:55.693 --> 39:57.661
and we'll say we found the kid
in the bushes, or whatever.

39:57.728 --> 39:58.786
(SCOFFS)

39:58.863 --> 40:00.831
It's either this, real quiet,

40:00.898 --> 40:03.128
or it's a thousand fucking cops
kicking your door in,

40:03.200 --> 40:05.691
putting their fat knees in your neck.

40:09.173 --> 40:10.435
Hold up.

40:12.743 --> 40:14.836
Whoa. Whoa.

40:16.113 --> 40:17.740
What the fuck is this?

40:19.049 --> 40:20.641
Lift up your shirt.

40:21.786 --> 40:24.550
- Come on, man.
- Motherfucker, you heard me.

40:25.289 --> 40:27.018
Lift up your shirt.

40:28.058 --> 40:31.619
- It ain't like that, Cheese.
- My CC, I ain't down with you.

40:31.929 --> 40:33.692
Lift up your shirt.

40:36.133 --> 40:37.623
(SIGHING)

40:39.970 --> 40:41.528
You, too, baby.
Ain't no gender immunity.

40:41.605 --> 40:43.095
Let me see some tit.

40:49.447 --> 40:52.041
Don't ever come in my spot like that.

40:52.149 --> 40:53.639
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

40:55.352 --> 40:56.979
You got my money,

40:57.054 --> 41:00.854
you leave that shit in the mailbox
on your ass way out, you feel me?

41:00.958 --> 41:02.858
Some other motherfuckers
let fool rob on them.

41:02.927 --> 41:05.157
I don't play scrimmage.

41:05.229 --> 41:07.459
But I don't fuck with no kids.

41:10.768 --> 41:16.206
And if that girl only hope is you,
well, I pray for her,

41:16.273 --> 41:18.138
'cause she's gone, baby.

41:19.276 --> 41:20.436
Gone.

41:30.855 --> 41:32.914
Cheese, if you ever
disrespect her again like that,

41:32.990 --> 41:35.584
I'm gonna pull your fucking card.

41:35.659 --> 41:36.785
Okay?

41:42.666 --> 41:45.294
So you're saying you didn't do it, fine.

41:45.369 --> 41:48.429
We'll take your money,
and we'll be on our way.

41:49.373 --> 41:51.398
But if it turns out you're lying,

41:51.475 --> 41:54.137
I'm going to spend every nickel
of that money to fuck you up.

41:54.211 --> 41:55.906
I'm gonna bribe cops to go after you,

41:55.980 --> 41:58.448
I'm gonna pay guys
to go after your weak fucking crew,

41:58.516 --> 42:01.610
and I'm gonna tell everyone I know
that you're a CI and a rat.

42:01.685 --> 42:03.778
And I know a lot of people.

42:04.421 --> 42:06.548
And after that, you're gonna wish
you had listened to me,

42:06.624 --> 42:09.388
'cause your shitty, pool-hall,
crime-syndicate headquarters

42:09.460 --> 42:10.825
is gonna get raided.

42:10.895 --> 42:13.420
And your doped-up bitches
are gonna get sent back to Laos,

42:13.497 --> 42:15.931
and this fucking retard right here
is gonna be testifying against you

42:16.000 --> 42:18.400
for a reduced sentence while you're
getting cornholed in your cell

42:18.469 --> 42:20.164
by a gang of crackers.

42:22.339 --> 42:24.273
'Cause from what I heard,

42:24.341 --> 42:27.640
you guys that get sent up Concord
for killing kids,

42:27.711 --> 42:29.508
life a motherfucker.

42:40.891 --> 42:44.327
If I see you again,
I'm gonna get discourteous on you.

42:56.640 --> 42:58.835
And get that sausage off my lawn.

42:59.743 --> 43:02.473
- NICK: Well, what happened?
- He said he didn't know anything,

43:02.546 --> 43:05.310
but if you had his money,
you could put it in his mailbox.

43:05.382 --> 43:08.283
- That's what he told you?
- That's it.

43:08.352 --> 43:10.343
Nothing else?

43:10.421 --> 43:13.788
Yeah. He said that he wanted
you two off his lawn.

43:13.857 --> 43:15.119
(CHUCKLES)

43:15.192 --> 43:17.092
I thought you said
you knew this fucking guy.

43:17.161 --> 43:19.391
Half the guys he knows
are degenerates.

43:19.463 --> 43:21.090
Yeah, you know
what the other half are?

43:21.165 --> 43:24.191
- What?
- Cops. Don't hold it against me.

43:24.802 --> 43:29.171
No, no. I won't hold it against you.

43:30.608 --> 43:33.042
You know what I'll hold against you?

43:33.110 --> 43:37.604
We had one chance to make this deal.
You said you knew him.

43:37.681 --> 43:40.673
You said you could do it
and you fucked it up.

43:41.352 --> 43:43.718
Now I gotta get a warrant for a tap,
start surveillance,

43:43.787 --> 43:45.652
hope to Christ we get lucky.

43:45.723 --> 43:47.816
You know, if Amanda
dies because of this,

43:48.492 --> 43:49.823
(SIGHING)

43:49.893 --> 43:51.758
I won't have to hold it against you.

43:53.063 --> 43:56.499
You'll hold it against yourself
for a long, long time.

44:19.657 --> 44:21.557
(EXHALES)

44:23.027 --> 44:25.257
Hope we didn't fuck this up.

44:30.367 --> 44:32.028
(PHONE RINGING)

44:34.705 --> 44:36.969
- Yeah.
- Cheese called in.

44:37.041 --> 44:39.874
Says he'll take the deal with Amanda,
but he wants to go tonight.

44:39.943 --> 44:42.571
- Great.
- Well, it is and it isn't.

44:42.646 --> 44:45.342
They record calls at the station now.

44:45.416 --> 44:47.976
- Jack got a hold of the transcript.
- What does that mean?

44:48.052 --> 44:51.112
It means our badges are
basically fucking forfeit at this point.

44:51.188 --> 44:53.053
He wants you both down here, now.

44:53.123 --> 44:55.250
Oh, and, hey, Cheese said
he left something in a mailbox

44:55.325 --> 44:57.691
to prove that he's got Amanda.

45:19.149 --> 45:23.210
This is a transcript of a recorded call
that came in this morning.

45:26.457 --> 45:28.584
Care to read the highlighted portion?

45:30.728 --> 45:32.059
Aloud?

45:33.130 --> 45:34.495
Uh.

45:35.599 --> 45:40.002
(CLEARS THROAT) "Caller: Bitch,
you better have my money.

45:42.973 --> 45:45.100
"Detective Bressant: Who is this?

45:45.175 --> 45:48.736
"The caller:
You know who the fuck this is, fool...

45:48.812 --> 45:51.303
"Creole curse words.
If you want that girl back,

45:51.381 --> 45:53.849
"you need to meet me up
Quincy tonight.

45:53.917 --> 45:56.442
"Fuck around for a minute
and I'll throw that girl in the lake."

45:56.520 --> 46:00.115
The lake he refers to is the water
in the abandoned quarry.

46:01.458 --> 46:05.861
Detective Bressant goes on to make
an unauthorized ransom arrangement

46:05.929 --> 46:09.660
to exchange Amanda McCready
for $ 130,000 tonight

46:09.733 --> 46:11.792
in just that location.

46:12.770 --> 46:16.365
After some discussion,
Detective Bressant was kind enough

46:16.440 --> 46:18.135
to produce this.

46:18.208 --> 46:20.369
Recognize it?

46:20.444 --> 46:23.538
The four of you have involved me
in an illegal activity

46:23.614 --> 46:27.106
without my knowledge or consent,
and I don't fucking appreciate it.

46:27.184 --> 46:30.676
- You don't have to be a part of it, sir.
- The hell I don't.

46:30.754 --> 46:32.483
If I delay this now, after this agreement,

46:32.556 --> 46:35.252
I just further endanger
the life of that child.

46:35.325 --> 46:38.192
Does that sound like something
you expect me to do?

46:38.262 --> 46:39.593
No, sir.

46:40.430 --> 46:42.091
I went in there. I'll accept responsibility.

46:42.166 --> 46:44.031
You'll accept nothing!

46:44.301 --> 46:46.826
Don't come in here
trying to get noble, boy.

46:49.006 --> 46:50.803
Let me see that note.

46:58.015 --> 46:59.175
My God.

47:02.386 --> 47:04.377
REMY: He wants to separate us.

47:04.454 --> 47:07.184
The note instructs you guys to be
on the east side and wait for Amanda,

47:07.257 --> 47:10.590
me and Nick to be at the clearing
by the edge with the money.

47:10.661 --> 47:13.459
Once Amanda's turned over to you,
you give us a call on the radio,

47:13.530 --> 47:15.327
we turn over the cash.

47:16.767 --> 47:19.565
- Who's he likely to bring with him?
- Chris Mullen.

47:19.636 --> 47:21.763
He was at the club
when we made the offer.

47:21.839 --> 47:23.466
What do you know about him?

47:23.540 --> 47:26.475
It was probably him
who killed Ray for Cheese.

47:26.543 --> 47:27.737
If I had to guess.

47:27.811 --> 47:30.575
All right.
Nobody else knows about this, right?

47:30.647 --> 47:33.081
- I don't know.
- Yes?

47:33.150 --> 47:37.246
I'm asking if keeping it quiet is better
for Amanda or is it better for us?

47:38.589 --> 47:41.615
Do you have any children,
Miss Gennaro?

47:41.692 --> 47:43.250
No, sir.

47:44.761 --> 47:49.255
My only child was murdered.
She was 12. Did you hear about it?

47:51.068 --> 47:52.296
What you probably didn't hear,

47:52.369 --> 47:53.597
and what I hope
you never have to deal with,

47:53.670 --> 47:57.106
Miss Gennaro, is what that feels like.
What I have to deal with.

47:57.975 --> 48:01.706
Knowing that my little girl likely died

48:01.778 --> 48:04.406
crying out for me
to come and save her.

48:05.349 --> 48:06.976
And I never did.

48:07.718 --> 48:13.987
My little girl died afraid and alone
in a shallow ditch bank

48:14.057 --> 48:17.618
by the side of the road
not 10 minutes from my house.

48:21.031 --> 48:23.864
I know what it feels like to lose a child.

48:26.503 --> 48:29.666
Now, damn it, you force my hand

48:29.740 --> 48:32.038
and then you question
the way I handle it.

48:32.109 --> 48:34.304
No one's questioning you, sir.

48:34.378 --> 48:37.142
I honor my child with this division.

48:38.348 --> 48:41.249
So that no parent
has to go through what I've known.

48:42.319 --> 48:44.184
This child.

48:47.291 --> 48:48.952
That's all I care about.

48:49.860 --> 48:51.885
I'm gonna bring her home.

49:06.143 --> 49:07.337
(EXHALES)

49:07.678 --> 49:10.306
Why'd he bring us all the way up here?

49:12.482 --> 49:15.076
I don't know. It's big. It's dark.
It's easy to get away.

49:15.152 --> 49:16.210
No.

49:18.889 --> 49:20.857
They're gonna kill her.

49:44.247 --> 49:48.377
NICK: This asshole could've found
some level fucking ground somewhere.

49:48.452 --> 49:52.479
This is where we part ways.
You guys'll be on top of that cliff.

49:52.556 --> 49:54.581
We'll be right across from you.

49:54.658 --> 49:57.718
Give us a call on the radio
when you have her.

49:58.795 --> 50:01.286
- We will.
- Well, good luck.

50:04.201 --> 50:05.532
Let's go.

50:44.474 --> 50:46.101
How are they gonna
get Amanda up here?

50:46.176 --> 50:47.609
(GUN FIRING)

50:47.677 --> 50:49.338
NICK ON RADIO: Ambush! Ambush!

50:49.513 --> 50:53.381
Hey, Remy! Fucking Cheese!
Where is she?

50:53.450 --> 50:54.474
(ANGIE GRUNTING)

50:54.551 --> 50:59.386
NICK ON RADIO: There she is.
I can see her. It ain't the way it is!

50:59.456 --> 51:00.923
(CLAMORING)

51:00.991 --> 51:03.050
Someone hit Cheese!

51:03.760 --> 51:05.159
REMY: You sure you heard something?
NICK: Yes!

51:05.228 --> 51:06.786
- Over there!
- ANGIE: What happened?

51:06.863 --> 51:09.559
NICK: I don't know. I heard a splash.
Down there!

51:09.633 --> 51:10.622
REMY: Somebody took Cheese out,

51:10.700 --> 51:12.133
- and then all hell broke loose.
- ANGIE: Where's Amanda?

51:12.202 --> 51:13.362
- Shots were fired from over there.
- NICK: I don't know!

51:13.437 --> 51:14.461
Something went in the water!

51:14.538 --> 51:15.527
- What?
- You sure you heard something?

51:15.605 --> 51:16.936
- Yeah, something went in, but I...
- Where did it go?

51:17.007 --> 51:18.474
There! Right there!

51:18.542 --> 51:19.566
Oh, my God.

51:19.643 --> 51:20.701
(GASPS)

51:20.777 --> 51:22.005
Oh, no.

51:34.157 --> 51:36.057
NICK: Jesus Christ!

51:37.828 --> 51:39.227
(GASPING)

51:39.296 --> 51:40.661
(GRUNTING)

52:24.941 --> 52:28.172
WOMAN ON PA: Paging
Dr. Goldsburn. Dr. Goldsburn to ICU.

52:36.153 --> 52:37.552
(DOOR OPENS)

52:42.526 --> 52:43.891
(EXHALES)

52:49.599 --> 52:51.794
- Hi.
- Hi.

52:53.069 --> 52:56.766
- How's the leg?
- It'll be fine.

52:59.943 --> 53:01.740
They find anything?

53:04.014 --> 53:08.849
- They got divers in there now.
- She could still be alive.

53:10.887 --> 53:14.721
Maybe she's hiding.
She could be stuck.

53:14.791 --> 53:15.985
Right?

53:18.528 --> 53:20.553
I don't think so.

53:22.832 --> 53:24.697
(SIGHING)

53:32.142 --> 53:33.803
(PATRICK MUMBLES)

53:34.878 --> 53:36.470
(SNIFFLES)

53:36.746 --> 53:38.577
(MAN CHATTERING ON TV)

53:39.049 --> 53:40.038
Hey...

53:40.116 --> 53:42.209
MAN ON TV: He's ever seen
in all his years,

53:42.285 --> 53:46.278
on a little girl called Amanda
and a doll named Mirabelle.

53:46.356 --> 53:49.348
JACK ON TV: This quarry is
extremely deep and treacherous.

53:50.193 --> 53:54.562
All too often,
she keeps that which she takes in.

53:54.631 --> 53:56.360
MAN ON TV: A sad end
to that story, Suzanne.

53:56.433 --> 53:57.900
WOMAN ON TV: It sure is, Phil.

