He says he loves her,
tells Mike Snell to go fuck himself,

01:17:28.644 --> 01:17:29.736
and puts in for a transfer.

01:17:29.811 --> 01:17:30.835
What, to Doyle?

01:17:30.912 --> 01:17:34.609
Doyle brought Remy
from Louisiana, back in '72.

01:17:34.683 --> 01:17:38.119
You don't think that Remy's
dirty, though, do you?

01:17:38.186 --> 01:17:40.051
What's "dirty"?

01:17:41.623 --> 01:17:44.922
- I know he planted evidence once.
- Oh, you do?

01:17:46.528 --> 01:17:48.462
Yeah. Why?

01:17:48.530 --> 01:17:51.090
Look, man. CSI is killing us out here.

01:17:51.166 --> 01:17:54.693
Every other juror, all they wanna know
is where the microfibers are.

01:17:54.770 --> 01:17:56.567
Certain people are workers.

01:17:56.638 --> 01:17:58.265
Don't wanna plant it,
but you know how it is.

01:17:58.340 --> 01:18:00.501
So they don't mind it.

01:18:02.511 --> 01:18:06.140
So tell me something,
what you fucking with him for?

01:18:07.683 --> 01:18:10.083
He lied to me.

01:18:10.152 --> 01:18:12.416
I can't think of one reason
big enough for him to lie

01:18:12.487 --> 01:18:15.115
that's small enough not to matter.

01:18:20.095 --> 01:18:21.756
All right, look.

01:18:21.830 --> 01:18:26.290
I know one thing, but it's third party,
so you gotta play it like that.

01:18:26.368 --> 01:18:29.394
Helene and Ray took Cheese's money
back in June, right?

01:18:29.471 --> 01:18:30.495
Yeah.

01:18:30.572 --> 01:18:33.541
One week later,
Remy goes to a cop in DCU

01:18:33.608 --> 01:18:36.076
asking if anybody knew
who robbed Cheese.

01:18:36.144 --> 01:18:37.338
So what?

01:18:37.412 --> 01:18:39.175
So my informant tells me,

01:18:39.247 --> 01:18:42.774
Cheese didn't even know
he got robbed until two weeks later.

01:18:43.051 --> 01:18:45.918
So Remy knew Cheese got robbed
before Cheese did?

01:18:45.987 --> 01:18:47.887
How'd he know that?

01:18:49.057 --> 01:18:50.854
Let me tell you something.

01:18:50.926 --> 01:18:51.984
You better think long and hard

01:18:52.060 --> 01:18:55.052
before you start running around here
investigating the police.

01:18:55.130 --> 01:18:59.965
You try and take food out their mouths,
and they will fuck you up.

01:19:02.571 --> 01:19:04.471
Thanks for the steak.

01:19:05.140 --> 01:19:06.869
All right.

01:19:20.288 --> 01:19:21.687
Hey.

01:19:23.725 --> 01:19:25.215
I got it.

01:19:25.861 --> 01:19:27.795
PATRICK ON PHONE:
We need to talk to you, Lionel.

01:19:27.863 --> 01:19:29.296
LIONEL ON PHONE:
About what?

01:19:29.364 --> 01:19:32.094
About the acoustics in your apartment.

01:19:32.167 --> 01:19:33.725
What?

01:19:33.802 --> 01:19:35.702
Oh, we live
in a three-decker, too, Lionel.

01:19:35.771 --> 01:19:37.636
I got nothing to talk about.

01:19:37.706 --> 01:19:40.800
Well, that's fine.
We can talk to the state police.

01:19:41.910 --> 01:19:44.071
Meet me at Murphy's Law.

01:20:02.497 --> 01:20:04.021
LIONEL ON PHONE: I don't meet him
down Murphy's,

01:20:04.099 --> 01:20:05.396
he's gonna call the staties.

01:20:05.467 --> 01:20:07.833
REMY ON PHONE: He's putting a
move on you. Don't go down there.

01:20:08.436 --> 01:20:09.994
I can handle Patrick Kenzie.

01:20:10.071 --> 01:20:11.766
- This is an oath we took.
- I started this.

01:20:11.840 --> 01:20:13.808
- This has to be protected.
- I got things to protect, too.

01:20:13.875 --> 01:20:14.967
- Listen to me!
- All right, Remy.

01:20:15.043 --> 01:20:17.409
You leave that house,
you're an enemy to me.

01:20:17.479 --> 01:20:19.811
- Just trust me, all right?
- No! Trust me!

01:20:19.881 --> 01:20:24.545
Where I come from,
you die with your secrets!

01:20:50.779 --> 01:20:53.213
How long have you known Remy?

01:20:53.281 --> 01:20:56.409
Detective Bressant? Just in...

01:20:56.484 --> 01:20:59.749
Met him through
the investigation of Amanda.

01:20:59.821 --> 01:21:01.789
- That's it?
- Yeah.

01:21:05.193 --> 01:21:07.354
How long you known Remy?

01:21:08.396 --> 01:21:09.590
What is this?

01:21:09.664 --> 01:21:12.633
They got the Internet, now, Lionel.

01:21:12.701 --> 01:21:15.067
You know how it is in town.
Everybody knows everybody.

01:21:15.136 --> 01:21:17.604
No. Everybody don't know everybody.

01:21:17.672 --> 01:21:19.299
- What're you talking about?
- Why you lying?

01:21:19.374 --> 01:21:20.363
I'm not.

01:21:20.442 --> 01:21:23.206
You bragged about taking a hard bust
on the first day we met you.

01:21:23.278 --> 01:21:24.836
- No, I didn't.
- Bullshit.

01:21:24.913 --> 01:21:27.404
You're hiding something, Lionel,
and you better fucking tell it,

01:21:27.482 --> 01:21:30.417
'cause you came to our house
and you asked us for help.

01:21:30.485 --> 01:21:32.715
And we killed ourselves
trying to save Amanda.

01:21:32.787 --> 01:21:34.618
And I know you ain't being 100%
with me right now,

01:21:34.689 --> 01:21:36.623
and it's really fucking pissing me off
that you're lying,

01:21:36.691 --> 01:21:39.159
so you better interrupt me at any time,
'cause I'm about to lose...

01:21:39.227 --> 01:21:42.128
Okay. Fine, fine. All right?
Don't have a heart attack.

01:21:43.298 --> 01:21:45.425
I haven't been honest with you.

01:21:45.500 --> 01:21:48.469
It's just not something I'm proud of.
You know?

01:21:48.536 --> 01:21:51.403
I got in a bar fight back in the day.

01:21:51.473 --> 01:21:52.701
The other guy cracked his skull.

01:21:52.774 --> 01:21:55.265
At some point,
I must've said, "I'll kill you."

01:21:55.343 --> 01:21:59.712
So they had me up for attempted.
It's my word against this other guy's.

01:21:59.781 --> 01:22:02.545
Witness testified to my version
and the jury believed him.

01:22:02.617 --> 01:22:05.518
- 'Cause he was a cop.
- Yeah, he testified for me.

01:22:05.587 --> 01:22:07.248
So you knew Detective Bressant.

01:22:07.322 --> 01:22:09.620
- It's not like we were best friends.
- But you lied.

01:22:09.691 --> 01:22:12.922
- Why did you call Remy?
- He's a cop.

01:22:12.994 --> 01:22:14.859
- That's not why you called him, Lionel.
- Come on.

01:22:14.930 --> 01:22:16.795
It's a small place.
You heard them arguing.

01:22:16.865 --> 01:22:18.457
- They were being loud.
- Who? Who... Who...

01:22:18.533 --> 01:22:22.936
So you called Remy, and you and him
took Amanda to blackmail your sister.

01:22:23.004 --> 01:22:24.369
(SCOFFS)

01:22:26.041 --> 01:22:27.736
Why would I do that?

01:22:27.809 --> 01:22:30.835
I don't know, Lionel. I really don't know.

01:22:30.912 --> 01:22:33.904
Maybe because after all the
"I put the fucking plug in the jug,"

01:22:33.982 --> 01:22:35.973
and the "count your blessings"
and the "watch your language,"

01:22:36.051 --> 01:22:38.212
you're just like everybody else.

01:22:38.286 --> 01:22:40.186
You saw a bag of money
and you wanted it.

01:22:40.255 --> 01:22:41.847
And you thought
you could get away with it.

01:22:41.923 --> 01:22:44.050
But Bea called the media
and made a big thing of it.

01:22:44.125 --> 01:22:46.491
And then she called us,
and then you were fucked.

01:22:46.561 --> 01:22:48.688
The case is closed, Patrick.
The case is closed.

01:22:48.763 --> 01:22:51.061
Coke-dealing Haitian's
a pretty easy target for a frame.

01:22:51.132 --> 01:22:52.429
- Lionel?
- Excuse me.

01:22:52.500 --> 01:22:53.558
- Look at me.
- Okay. Excuse me.

01:22:53.635 --> 01:22:55.262
You took your niece,
and you laid it off on a black guy.

01:22:55.337 --> 01:22:56.565
- Pardon me.
- Lionel, tell me what happened.

01:22:56.638 --> 01:22:58.765
Can I get some service?

01:22:58.840 --> 01:23:00.205
Yeah.

01:23:04.012 --> 01:23:05.411
(EXHALES)

01:23:06.982 --> 01:23:08.381
What?

01:23:09.985 --> 01:23:13.113
- Three shots of Cutty and a tallboy.
- Yeah.

01:23:13.188 --> 01:23:14.678
Thank you.

01:23:15.991 --> 01:23:18.016
Just give me a second.

01:23:49.290 --> 01:23:52.225
Twenty-three years
is something, right?

01:24:04.839 --> 01:24:06.238
Go.

01:24:10.345 --> 01:24:13.542
I come up to check on Amanda.
She was alone as usual.

01:24:15.817 --> 01:24:18.342
I was reading her a story
when Helene and Ray come home.

01:24:18.420 --> 01:24:19.512
They didn't know I was there.

01:24:19.587 --> 01:24:23.114
Stop fucking yelling,
my daughter's sleeping in there.

01:24:23.191 --> 01:24:24.749
(ARGUING)

01:24:25.260 --> 01:24:27.888
They started talking about how
they'd robbed this drug dealer.

01:24:27.962 --> 01:24:30.055
You know what he's fucking gonna do
if he finds out?

01:24:30.131 --> 01:24:31.894
What's the monkey gonna do?

01:24:31.966 --> 01:24:33.297
- Oh, you know...
- I'm not...

01:24:33.368 --> 01:24:36.531
And they were talking
about leaving the state.

01:24:36.604 --> 01:24:38.071
So I called Remy and told him.

01:24:38.139 --> 01:24:40.801
There's another drug run
up to Nashua. Taking cocaine...

01:24:40.875 --> 01:24:42.536
And then what?

01:24:46.314 --> 01:24:47.440
We took her.

01:24:50.285 --> 01:24:53.015
Remy laid out this plan.
It seemed easy.

01:24:53.088 --> 01:24:55.955
We take her, force Helene and Ray
to cough up the cash,

01:24:56.024 --> 01:24:58.049
then we put her back. You know?

01:24:58.126 --> 01:25:00.185
Amanda gets to spend
a weekend in the country.

01:25:00.261 --> 01:25:01.785
My sister learns a lesson.

01:25:02.130 --> 01:25:04.894
And fuck it, everybody gets paid
on top of it.

01:25:04.966 --> 01:25:07.935
I got no problem taking money
from a guy like Cheese.

01:25:08.002 --> 01:25:09.560
They were gonna handle the cops.

01:25:09.637 --> 01:25:11.867
But Bea, she went nuts.

01:25:11.940 --> 01:25:14.500
Started calling the papers. Hired you.

01:25:14.576 --> 01:25:16.908
Lionel don't want me coming here,
now you don't want the job?

01:25:16.978 --> 01:25:20.971
But once you found the money,
they had Amanda and the money.

01:25:21.049 --> 01:25:25.179
So they decided to set up
a fake exchange for you to witness.

01:25:25.253 --> 01:25:27.915
They got Chris Mullen
to set up Cheese at the quarry.

01:25:27.989 --> 01:25:31.584
15K and a chance to be the boss.

01:25:34.395 --> 01:25:36.693
Cheese figured out
what was happening.

01:25:36.764 --> 01:25:40.222
Even though it was too late,
he started shooting.

01:25:40.301 --> 01:25:42.235
Panicking.

01:25:44.873 --> 01:25:47.205
And she just fell. I mean, she just...

01:25:47.275 --> 01:25:48.936
She fell in.

01:25:50.411 --> 01:25:52.038
She's gone.

01:25:52.113 --> 01:25:54.308
It was an accident.
It was just an accident.

01:25:54.382 --> 01:25:56.577
She was your sister's kid, Lionel.

01:25:58.486 --> 01:26:02.149
- Your sister's child.
- You think I don't miss her?

01:26:02.223 --> 01:26:04.783
She was more my kid than Helene's.

01:26:05.894 --> 01:26:09.990
Last summer, Helene and Dottie
took Amanda to the beach.

01:26:10.165 --> 01:26:14.295
It was a real hot day.
Amanda fell asleep.

01:26:14.736 --> 01:26:17.261
They left her in the car
while they go off into the dunes,

01:26:17.338 --> 01:26:19.101
smoke a doobie with some guys.

01:26:19.174 --> 01:26:20.903
Two hours.

01:26:22.644 --> 01:26:25.340
Amanda literally roasted.

01:26:26.614 --> 01:26:28.104
She was three.

01:26:30.885 --> 01:26:35.151
Later on, I was holding her,
trying to help her get to sleep.

01:26:36.191 --> 01:26:40.855
My little Amanda, she was so hot.

01:26:43.097 --> 01:26:46.066
She felt like something
just come out of the oven.

01:26:47.402 --> 01:26:49.700
Like a fucking pot roast.

01:26:51.839 --> 01:26:54.171
So don't feel too sorry for my sister.

01:26:54.242 --> 01:26:58.008
Because she never gave a shit
about anyone but herself.

01:26:59.147 --> 01:27:00.045
(DOOR BANGS)

01:27:00.114 --> 01:27:02.947
Bartender. Open the safe. Now.

01:27:04.619 --> 01:27:08.578
Everybody needs to shut up and stay
calm. On the floor. On the floor!

01:27:08.656 --> 01:27:10.317
- Hands on your head. Do it.
- MAN: Oh, my God.

01:27:10.391 --> 01:27:11.983
Everybody stays calm,
this'll be over in a minute.

01:27:12.060 --> 01:27:14.995
Hey, do you know
whose bar this is, shithead?

01:27:15.563 --> 01:27:18.430
Or you can get wise, it's up to you.

01:27:21.169 --> 01:27:22.966
What did you say?

01:27:23.738 --> 01:27:25.763
You're a talker, huh?

01:27:25.840 --> 01:27:27.398
Just keep revving, motherfucker.

01:27:27.475 --> 01:27:29.568
WOMAN: Don't antagonize him.
He's got a gun.

01:27:29.644 --> 01:27:32.977
- Oh, just keep yapping away.
- I didn't say nothing.

01:27:33.047 --> 01:27:34.912
You should learn
to keep your mouth shut.

01:27:34.983 --> 01:27:36.416
WOMAN: Shut the fuck up,
for Christ's sake.

01:27:36.484 --> 01:27:39.214
- Just keep talking, pal.
- I didn't say nothing.

01:27:39.287 --> 01:27:40.652
Close your eyes.

01:27:40.722 --> 01:27:41.848
- Fuck!
- Remy Bressant.

01:27:41.923 --> 01:27:44.255
Amanda McCready
was taken by Remy Bressant.

01:27:44.325 --> 01:27:47.055
Oh, fuck, God. Amanda McCready
was taken by Remy Bressant!

01:27:47.128 --> 01:27:48.959
- Wait. Wait. Jesus.
- PATRICK: Remy Bressant.

01:27:49.030 --> 01:27:50.588
God damn it. Remy Bressant!

01:27:50.665 --> 01:27:51.723
Amanda McCready was taken

01:27:51.799 --> 01:27:52.925
- by Remy Bressant.
- Jesus. I told him.

01:27:53.001 --> 01:27:55.492
I told him we took her for ransom.
I told him. I told him, Remy.

01:27:55.570 --> 01:27:59.006
Please, I told him we took her
for ransom. I did it.

01:27:59.073 --> 01:28:00.938
Remy, please.

01:28:01.175 --> 01:28:02.642
Please.

01:28:06.281 --> 01:28:07.646
(GUN FIRES)

01:28:12.287 --> 01:28:14.084
(GRUNTING)

01:28:20.928 --> 01:28:22.793
Are you all right?

01:28:22.864 --> 01:28:23.888
(PANTING)

01:28:23.965 --> 01:28:24.989
Stay with him.

01:29:27.362 --> 01:29:29.125
Drop your gun.

01:29:30.865 --> 01:29:32.560
Put it down!

01:29:37.305 --> 01:29:40.797
That bartender wasn't fucking around.

01:29:50.451 --> 01:29:51.975
What did you do?

01:29:52.854 --> 01:29:54.344
Did you get her killed?

01:29:57.225 --> 01:29:58.920
Say yes.

01:30:03.898 --> 01:30:05.229
Say yes.

01:30:06.167 --> 01:30:07.634
Say yes!

01:30:08.536 --> 01:30:12.700
What're you gonna do? Shoot me?
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:30:20.548 --> 01:30:22.573
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:30:27.054 --> 01:30:29.079
She was a child.

01:30:31.225 --> 01:30:33.125
I love children.

01:31:09.964 --> 01:31:13.559
Why would I expose a conspiracy
that I was a part of?

01:31:14.969 --> 01:31:18.496
I mean, did Lionel contradict
anything I've said?

01:31:19.740 --> 01:31:22.971
Did any of the witnesses at the bar
contradict anything I've said?

01:31:23.044 --> 01:31:26.707
A police officer was killed today.
That's not looked on lightly.

01:31:26.781 --> 01:31:28.976
Is corruption looked on lightly?

01:31:29.050 --> 01:31:30.711
Is a little girl getting killed
looked on lightly?

01:31:30.785 --> 01:31:32.013
OFFICER: Whoa, hold on.

01:31:32.086 --> 01:31:34.520
You charge people money
as a detective.

01:31:34.589 --> 01:31:38.525
Now, you're at the quarry
the other night, right?

01:31:38.593 --> 01:31:41.528
And you have no idea
that this is a setup?

01:31:41.596 --> 01:31:43.996
You're baffled. Right?

01:31:45.533 --> 01:31:49.993
No, because, strange as it might seem,

01:31:50.071 --> 01:31:53.302
I believe the police
when they tell me something.

01:31:54.008 --> 01:31:55.236
You're a fresh prick. You know that?

01:31:55.309 --> 01:31:57.539
And because I had a ransom note
and Amanda McCready's blanket

01:31:57.612 --> 01:31:58.704
put in my mailbox.

01:31:58.779 --> 01:32:01.805
And because I read a transcript of
a call that Cheese put into the station.

01:32:01.883 --> 01:32:02.975
A 911 call?

01:32:03.050 --> 01:32:06.110
No, it was a call
Cheese made to the station.

01:32:06.187 --> 01:32:07.484
To Remy Bressant at the station.

01:32:07.555 --> 01:32:09.614
Or that Chris Mullen made,
pretending to be Cheese.

01:32:09.690 --> 01:32:11.487
Or whatever the fuck it was,
but it was recorded,

01:32:11.559 --> 01:32:13.459
and there was a call.

01:32:13.528 --> 01:32:15.462
We don't record calls
coming into the station,

01:32:15.530 --> 01:32:18.328
and we don't do transcripts, smart guy.

01:32:20.434 --> 01:32:22.994
OFFICER: So, did you hear a tape?

01:32:24.372 --> 01:32:26.670
- No, I didn't hear a tape.
- Okay.

01:32:26.741 --> 01:32:28.971
Did you see a transcript?

01:32:33.714 --> 01:32:36.274
No, I must've remembered it wrong.

01:32:46.527 --> 01:32:47.994
Kids forgive.

01:32:48.062 --> 01:32:49.552
What do they get for it?

01:32:49.630 --> 01:32:52.064
Amanda literally roasted.

01:33:01.375 --> 01:33:02.569
LIONEL: You think I don't miss her.

01:33:02.643 --> 01:33:05.077
She was more my kid than Helene's.

01:33:05.146 --> 01:33:07.273
I love children.

01:33:11.786 --> 01:33:16.018
This is the kind of thing that if you do,
Patrick, you wanna be sure.

01:33:18.292 --> 01:33:20.021
Are you sure?

01:33:20.728 --> 01:33:22.127
No.

01:33:25.967 --> 01:33:27.832
Are you coming?

01:33:28.469 --> 01:33:29.766
No.

01:33:41.415 --> 01:33:44.145
DEVIN: Doyle brought Remy
from Louisiana back in '72.

01:33:44.218 --> 01:33:46.914
JACK: Care to read
the highlighted portion?

01:33:58.599 --> 01:34:00.931
Taking a trip?

01:34:01.002 --> 01:34:02.765
Patrick Kenzie.

01:34:04.372 --> 01:34:07.170
To what do I owe the pleasure?

01:34:07.241 --> 01:34:09.869
Remy Bressant died last night.

01:34:10.411 --> 01:34:13.437
I was told. It's a shame.

01:34:14.882 --> 01:34:19.478
Yeah, it's hard to understand.
Because he seemed like a good man.

01:34:19.553 --> 01:34:21.384
He was a good man.

01:34:22.723 --> 01:34:25.385
We don't know
why people do what they do.

01:34:25.726 --> 01:34:28.058
Everybody looks out his own window.

01:34:28.295 --> 01:34:30.456
And everyone's got their reasons.

01:34:32.466 --> 01:34:33.990
(DOOR OPENS)

01:34:40.875 --> 01:34:42.570
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:34:42.643 --> 01:34:43.940
- How are you?
- Good.

01:34:44.011 --> 01:34:46.070
REMY: Nick! They're firing at me.

01:34:46.147 --> 01:34:47.842
Nick, you hear me? You okay?
They're firing at me!

01:34:47.915 --> 01:34:49.075
NICK: Remy!

01:34:49.150 --> 01:34:51.414
- I heard something go in the water!
- Ambush! Ambush!

01:34:51.485 --> 01:34:54.386
- Something went in!
- Run. Remy. Run!

